1
00:00:33,660 --> 00:00:34,370
Stop!

2
00:00:34,370 --> 00:00:34,950
Dang!

3
00:00:34,950 --> 00:00:35,620
Get the cars!

4
00:00:35,620 --> 00:00:36,700
After them!

5
00:00:37,870 --> 00:00:39,330
What are you doing?!

6
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:40,330
Hurry up!

7
00:00:59,150 --> 00:01:01,490
<i>Keep up the good work!</i>

8
00:01:06,940 --> 00:01:09,740
There's 5 billion here
in non-sequential bills.

9
00:01:09,740 --> 00:01:11,990
Here's a shower of money! Take that!

10
00:01:11,990 --> 00:01:12,990
Whoa!

11
00:01:12,990 --> 00:01:14,910
Hot! Hot! Hot! Steaming hot!

12
00:01:14,910 --> 00:01:17,330
Bury me some more!

13
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:29,760
What's wrong, Lupin?

14
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:30,840
Let's dump it.

15
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:31,840
What?!

16
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:33,720
These are counterfeit.

17
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:35,390
Well-made, but still.

18
00:01:35,390 --> 00:01:36,470
They are?!

19
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:38,220
They can't be...

20
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:40,890
We swiped these from the
vault of a state-run casino.

21
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:42,810
They're Gothic bills.

22
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:43,940
Gothic bills?

23
00:01:43,940 --> 00:01:46,110
Those legendary counterfeits?

24
00:01:46,110 --> 00:01:49,360
So, they're even showing up
at state-run casinos now, huh?

25
00:01:49,690 --> 00:01:52,200
Jigen, that's it! That's our next job.

26
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:54,620
What do you say we party
hard to celebrate in advance?

27
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:57,370
Paaar-tay!

28
00:01:59,330 --> 00:02:01,330
Damn it!

29
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:02,960
Stupid things! Damn it! Damn it!

30
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,120
Damn it!

31
00:02:13,860 --> 00:02:21,080
<i>Lupin the Third: The Castle of Cagliostro</i>

32
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:35,450
<i>Searching out happiness</i>

33
00:02:36,790 --> 00:02:41,670
<i>Is how I want to make my way</i>

34
00:02:42,290 --> 00:02:48,720
<i>Even thorny paths and freezing cold nights</i>

35
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:54,720
<i>I want to traverse, the two of us together</i>

36
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:05,980
<i>The bleak heart of the traveler</i>

37
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:12,240
<i>Who will be there to embrace it?</i>

38
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:19,870
<i>Who will make those dreams come true?</i>

39
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:29,550
<i>A flame, it burns passionately</i>

40
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:36,520
<i>This love of mine</i>

41
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:42,350
<i>I want for you to understand, and you alone</i>

42
00:03:42,350 --> 00:03:48,490
<i>Wrap me up in the bond we share</i>

43
00:04:37,990 --> 00:04:41,200
I've never heard of this
Principality of Cagliostro.

44
00:04:41,660 --> 00:04:43,240
Population, 3,500.

45
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:46,450
It's the world's smallest state
to be a member of the UN.

46
00:04:46,450 --> 00:04:49,080
And it's where the Gothic
bills are coming from, huh?

47
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,750
It's a famous legend
among those in the know.

48
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:54,210
The black hole of the
world of counterfeit bills.

49
00:04:54,210 --> 00:04:56,000
Black hole?

50
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,010
The story goes that folks who
snoop around are never seen again.

51
00:04:59,630 --> 00:05:02,140
Huh. Scary.

52
00:05:03,430 --> 00:05:05,510
It's scary, so I'm going to sleep.

53
00:05:16,230 --> 00:05:16,900
Hey.

54
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:17,650
Hm?

55
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:35,290
What the heck?
This spare is totally bald.

56
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:54,150
Talk about peaceful.

57
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:08,740
What the...?

58
00:06:08,740 --> 00:06:09,490
Get in!

59
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:32,520
- So, who do we side with?
- The woman!

60
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:33,560
Thought so!

61
00:06:41,820 --> 00:06:42,690
The tires!

62
00:06:42,690 --> 00:06:43,610
Got it!

63
00:07:06,010 --> 00:07:08,220
Dang! That's no ordinary car!

64
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:18,060
Yowch!

65
00:07:18,060 --> 00:07:20,020
Now, this is getting interesting!

66
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:21,400
We're taking the lead!

67
00:07:38,670 --> 00:07:39,960
Took it!

68
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,920
The next shot won't
be any ordinary slug.

69
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,060
Yes!

70
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:10,160
Whoa, whoa, whoa...

71
00:08:10,410 --> 00:08:11,990
She's fainted.

72
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,460
That car's going to fall apart.

73
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:21,500
Take the wheel!

74
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,120
Whoa...

75
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:55,240
Whoa, whoa, whoa... Whoa!

76
00:09:32,610 --> 00:09:34,660
- No, let me go!
- H-Hey! No! No, no! Watch it!

77
00:09:34,660 --> 00:09:37,830
Down! Down! Down! Look down!
Look down, I said! Look down!

78
00:09:42,830 --> 00:09:45,290
Good, that's it.
Hold it right there.

79
00:09:58,390 --> 00:10:00,430
Whoops?!

80
00:10:16,370 --> 00:10:17,620
Hello?

81
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:18,910
Sir?!

82
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:38,560
Sir? Sir?

83
00:10:44,690 --> 00:10:45,940
I'm sorry.

84
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:05,370
Hey!

85
00:11:05,750 --> 00:11:06,880
Yo, Lupin.

86
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:08,920
Man, you're one sorry mess.

87
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,710
Uh, where'd my bride go?

88
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,050
Dear, oh, dear.

89
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:20,560
Damn it!

90
00:11:21,510 --> 00:11:24,430
All that for one measly girl?
Who the heck were they?

91
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,730
It's a ring.

92
00:11:32,730 --> 00:11:34,900
Hold on, I've seen this somewhere bef-

93
00:11:45,370 --> 00:11:46,290
What's gotten into you?!

94
00:11:46,290 --> 00:11:48,500
You suddenly got all weird
after seeing the ring!

95
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:49,710
Ow!

96
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:22,240
Hey, Lupin, is there
something at this old castle?

97
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:31,080
It's the same crest as
the one on the ring...

98
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:32,000
Lupin.

99
00:12:43,810 --> 00:12:46,350
It hasn't been too long since
this place was abandoned.

100
00:12:49,730 --> 00:12:50,730
A fire...

101
00:12:50,730 --> 00:12:51,650
Who's there?

102
00:12:51,650 --> 00:12:53,310
Just passing through.

103
00:12:53,310 --> 00:12:54,320
Tourists?

104
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,230
Well, yeah.

105
00:12:55,690 --> 00:12:59,990
I thought this was supposed to be
His Highness, the Prince's palace.

106
00:12:59,990 --> 00:13:01,240
It still is.

107
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:04,080
This place isn't for outsiders
to just come poking around.

108
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:06,290
You say this is the Prince's palace?

109
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:08,040
But it's an empty ruin.

110
00:13:09,710 --> 00:13:12,080
Because of the big fire seven years ago.

111
00:13:12,290 --> 00:13:14,750
Ever since the Prince
and his wife passed away,

112
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:17,170
it's been left to fall apart,
as you can see.

113
00:13:17,710 --> 00:13:20,680
That's odd.
The Prince is basically the king, right?

114
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:22,760
So, there's no king how?

115
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:26,220
There's a regent,
so it's apparently not a problem.

116
00:13:26,220 --> 00:13:27,310
Don't linger, you hear?

117
00:13:27,930 --> 00:13:28,930
Yeah, sure.

118
00:13:31,190 --> 00:13:32,310
Hey, Lupin.

119
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:56,190
You went and got all grown up...

120
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,010
What's up?

121
00:15:26,010 --> 00:15:27,800
Don't play dumb.

122
00:15:29,260 --> 00:15:32,470
- Quit acting cool and keeping your
problems to yourself! Out with it!
- No, no, no, no! You're choking me!

123
00:15:32,470 --> 00:15:34,680
No! No!

124
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:38,690
Talk! You gonna talk?!

125
00:15:38,690 --> 00:15:40,060
I'll talk, I'll talk, I'll talk, I'll talk...

126
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:08,050
That's the castle of the regent,
the Count of Cagliostro.

127
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:09,390
Look there.

128
00:16:10,050 --> 00:16:11,300
Lower.

129
00:16:12,810 --> 00:16:15,060
On the other side of the aqueduct.

130
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,560
Hm? It's that boat from earlier!

131
00:16:19,350 --> 00:16:21,400
So, the bride is inside that castle.

132
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:25,150
There's a sluice gate there.
It's exactly the same as it was back then.

133
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:27,860
You've snuck into that castle before?

134
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,410
It was over ten years ago.

135
00:16:31,410 --> 00:16:34,200
I was gonna solve the
mystery of the Gothic bills.

136
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,450
I was just a punk,
still wet behind the ears.

137
00:16:36,450 --> 00:16:38,000
And? How'd it go?

138
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,000
Oh, I got my butt kicked.

139
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,960
Turned tail and got out of there.

140
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:58,180
An autogyro, huh?
Talk about old-fashioned.

141
00:16:58,180 --> 00:16:59,310
That's the Count.

142
00:16:59,310 --> 00:17:01,560
- Huh?
- Come on, let's go look for an inn or something.

143
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,230
Hey...

144
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,230
Hey!

145
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,720
Jodot, that was careless.

146
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:33,300
My apologies, sir.

147
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:35,930
She was at a fitting
for her wedding attire

148
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:38,980
and the men were
not present at the time.

149
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:41,890
She's in the north tower now?

150
00:17:41,890 --> 00:17:45,570
Yes, sir. The drugs have
put her into a sound sleep.

151
00:17:50,650 --> 00:17:51,950
Foreigners...

152
00:17:51,950 --> 00:17:52,740
Yes, sir.

153
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:57,830
I am told that a pair of men
aided her during her escape.

154
00:17:58,910 --> 00:18:01,790
Find them.
Dispose of them how you will.

155
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:12,570
The ring is gone!

156
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,130
Get me Jodot!

157
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:55,990
These letters are from the Gothic
alphabet that no one uses anymore.

158
00:19:55,990 --> 00:19:57,200
The Gothic alphabet?

159
00:19:57,200 --> 00:20:00,990
"With light and shadow as one once more,
it shall surely be restored."

160
00:20:00,990 --> 00:20:03,040
1517.

161
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,870
The year is in Roman numerals.

162
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,000
So, this thing's 400 years old.

163
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:07,710
Sorry for the wait!

164
00:20:07,710 --> 00:20:09,500
Ooh, looks tasty.

165
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,710
You seem awfully preoccupied.
What are you looking at?

166
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:15,840
Oh, I picked up this old ring
and I was wondering if it's valuable.

167
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:17,510
Oh, my! It's pretty!

168
00:20:17,510 --> 00:20:19,430
This is the Lady Clarisse's crest.

169
00:20:19,430 --> 00:20:20,970
Clarisse...

170
00:20:20,970 --> 00:20:22,220
Look, that's her.

171
00:20:22,220 --> 00:20:23,760
That photo up there.

172
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,270
That's of when she was little, though.

173
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:29,230
She returned from the convent yesterday.

174
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:31,190
I imagine she's grown
into a fine young lady.

175
00:20:31,190 --> 00:20:32,650
The convent?

176
00:20:32,650 --> 00:20:33,940
Oh, you don't know?

177
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:38,490
I thought you'd come to see the Lady
Clarisse and the Count's wedding, too.

178
00:20:38,490 --> 00:20:39,530
Oh, so that's it!

179
00:20:39,530 --> 00:20:42,700
I was thinking there
were a lot of tourists here.

180
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,620
But I feel sorry for the Lady Clarisse.

181
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:47,580
The Count is a notorious
womanizer, you know.

182
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:49,620
Oh, my! Just like me!

183
00:20:49,620 --> 00:20:51,380
How does tonight sound?

184
00:20:51,380 --> 00:20:54,210
- Oh, please!
- Well? Well?

185
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:00,430
A spy for the Count,
just like we thought.

186
00:21:00,430 --> 00:21:02,850
His expression changed the
moment he saw the ring.

187
00:21:03,050 --> 00:21:04,680
Isn't the bride enough by herself?

188
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,310
He wants the ring, too!

189
00:21:06,310 --> 00:21:08,770
Not if I can help it!

190
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:13,650
You knew that girl we saw today
was the Princess, didn't you?!

191
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:15,820
Oh, didn't I clue you in?

192
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:34,340
"With light and shadow as one once
more, it shall surely be restored," huh?

193
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:39,920
You think it'll be some
treasure that's restored?

194
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:13,830
Why, you!

195
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:22,380
Wow, here comes the
whole kit and caboodle!

196
00:22:23,590 --> 00:22:24,840
You creep!

197
00:22:36,270 --> 00:22:37,730
The Magnum doesn't work on them!

198
00:22:37,730 --> 00:22:40,150
These guys are professional assassins.

199
00:22:57,130 --> 00:22:57,920
Hurry!

200
00:23:10,140 --> 00:23:13,810
- Whew! That sure got my blood pumping.
- That was a full-blown attack.

201
00:23:13,810 --> 00:23:15,520
This is one deep rabbit hole!

202
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,560
Yeah, this is getting interesting.

203
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:54,270
These didn't turn out well.

204
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:57,520
The quality has been on
a downward spiral lately.

205
00:23:57,770 --> 00:23:59,060
My apologies, sir.

206
00:23:59,060 --> 00:24:02,730
But if we continue to mass-produce
at our current pace...

207
00:24:03,070 --> 00:24:06,110
Redo these. And don't let
the delivery date slip, either.

208
00:24:06,110 --> 00:24:06,900
Yes, sir.

209
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,160
Who's there?

210
00:24:12,530 --> 00:24:14,870
I, Jodot, have never
blundered so greatly.

211
00:24:14,870 --> 00:24:17,000
The rats got away.

212
00:24:20,210 --> 00:24:23,170
Jodot, what's that piece
of paper on your back?

213
00:24:25,260 --> 00:24:26,470
Th... Th-This is...

214
00:24:26,670 --> 00:24:27,720
When did that get there?!

215
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:29,890
Lupin...

216
00:24:29,890 --> 00:24:31,550
It is an advance notice from Lupin.

217
00:24:32,140 --> 00:24:33,060
Read it.

218
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:35,140
Y-Yes, sir. Uh, but...

219
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:36,850
It's fine.

220
00:24:38,940 --> 00:24:42,940
"To the Count of lust and greed,
I will be taking your bride."

221
00:24:42,940 --> 00:24:45,860
"Expect me soon. Lupin the Third."

222
00:24:47,530 --> 00:24:49,110
You should be happy
about this, Jodot.

223
00:24:49,110 --> 00:24:49,860
Sir?

224
00:24:51,410 --> 00:24:53,120
Let us wait then.

225
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:55,410
For this Lupin to come.

226
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:40,460
Hey, you got here fast.

227
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:43,920
A job?

228
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:50,880
Goemon's here.

229
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,010
They're here, too.

230
00:25:52,010 --> 00:25:52,800
Huh?

231
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:54,090
Take a peek.

232
00:25:58,720 --> 00:25:59,640
Huh?!

233
00:26:00,520 --> 00:26:01,980
That's a Japanese police car!

234
00:26:01,980 --> 00:26:03,100
It's Zenigata.

235
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:03,770
What?!

236
00:26:05,980 --> 00:26:08,280
All personnel, disembark!

237
00:26:08,820 --> 00:26:10,240
Fall in!

238
00:26:13,820 --> 00:26:16,410
And now, the cast is complete.

239
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:28,590
Pardon me for interrupting your meal.

240
00:26:34,180 --> 00:26:36,510
I am Zenigata of the International
Criminal Police Organization.

241
00:26:36,510 --> 00:26:40,270
It was reported that you received an advance
notice from Lupin and that is why I am here.

242
00:26:42,020 --> 00:26:46,730
Oh, you mean that petty thief who's the
third-generation Arséne Lupin or whatever?

243
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:50,860
Is Interpol in the habit of disturbing
people's breakfasts for such things?

244
00:26:50,860 --> 00:26:53,490
Your Excellency, Lupin is
not to be underestimated.

245
00:26:53,490 --> 00:26:55,530
If he says he'll come,
he will, without fail.

246
00:26:55,530 --> 00:26:57,410
There are five days until your nuptials.

247
00:26:57,410 --> 00:27:00,620
I insist that you allow us
to patrol your castle.

248
00:27:03,410 --> 00:27:05,790
We have police in
this country, too, you know.

249
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:08,960
Though, we refer to them
more elegantly as gendarmes.

250
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,090
You called, sir?

251
00:27:11,340 --> 00:27:15,010
Gustav, cooperate
with this Japanese man.

252
00:27:15,010 --> 00:27:16,220
You're dismissed.

253
00:27:16,220 --> 00:27:16,930
Yes, sir!

254
00:27:16,930 --> 00:27:18,600
One more thing, Your Excellency.

255
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:22,100
Please tell me why that scoundrel
Lupin would be after your bride.

256
00:27:22,100 --> 00:27:23,230
Who knows?

257
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:26,980
Isn't investigating that
part of your job as well?

258
00:27:27,690 --> 00:27:29,020
Please excuse me.

259
00:27:32,820 --> 00:27:34,240
Are you sure about this, sir?

260
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:36,740
Allowing such a man
inside the castle would be...

261
00:27:36,740 --> 00:27:40,160
I don't care.
I have lots of friends at Interpol, too.

262
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:42,200
I'm sure he'll have
to withdraw in no time.

263
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:48,040
There's Zenigata. Talk about
a child of the early Showa era.

264
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:50,040
He is one hard worker.

265
00:28:00,180 --> 00:28:01,640
What is that?!

266
00:28:02,100 --> 00:28:03,970
Don't go any farther.

267
00:28:04,220 --> 00:28:05,060
What?

268
00:28:05,730 --> 00:28:06,890
Watch.

269
00:28:11,270 --> 00:28:14,110
If you don't want to die,
don't go wandering around.

270
00:28:14,110 --> 00:28:16,110
You let your men know that, too.

271
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:23,910
Inspector, we've detected
an antipersonnel radar as well.

272
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:25,830
I don't like this castle.

273
00:28:25,830 --> 00:28:28,710
They've got too many preventative
measures for amateurs.

274
00:28:32,090 --> 00:28:33,300
A woman?

275
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:35,420
Hold on now, don't say you're out.

276
00:28:35,420 --> 00:28:38,090
There's a woman mixed up in this,
but that's not the whole story.

277
00:28:38,090 --> 00:28:40,720
Is there something
special about this ring?

278
00:28:40,970 --> 00:28:45,220
Once we get the girl back from the
dirty ol' count, we'll know that, too.

279
00:28:45,470 --> 00:28:48,940
After all, these are monsters
that the Magnum can't touch.

280
00:28:48,940 --> 00:28:51,770
Between your blade
and this anti-tank rifle...

281
00:28:53,150 --> 00:28:55,150
Hey, Lupin, figured out
how to get in yet?

282
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:55,820
Nope.

283
00:28:55,820 --> 00:28:59,200
The place is incredible.
It's a nest full of lasers and radars.

284
00:28:59,740 --> 00:29:01,110
I see.

285
00:29:01,110 --> 00:29:02,570
We'll need a tank then...

286
00:29:02,570 --> 00:29:04,450
So you called Zenigata.

287
00:29:04,450 --> 00:29:05,240
What?

288
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:06,250
Is that true, Lupin?

289
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:09,920
Bingo! You've got good instincts.

290
00:29:10,290 --> 00:29:13,040
So, you will fight fire with fire.

291
00:29:18,130 --> 00:29:20,090
This is the Castle of Cagliostro.

292
00:29:20,090 --> 00:29:21,390
We're here.

293
00:29:21,390 --> 00:29:23,600
This Roman aqueduct
is still in use today.

294
00:29:24,140 --> 00:29:26,220
This is our only way in.

295
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:31,100
They use the Roman aqueduct to
draw water to the castle from the lake.

296
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:35,900
I see. And there won't
be any lasers underwater.

297
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:38,440
Goemon, you're the lookout.

298
00:29:45,910 --> 00:29:48,160
Watch out. There's a hole there.

299
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:01,340
Our first obstacle, huh?

300
00:30:02,880 --> 00:30:03,930
Here we go.

301
00:31:04,530 --> 00:31:06,410
L-Lupin!

302
00:31:25,340 --> 00:31:28,350
Oof, that's the machine room
of the clock tower.

303
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:30,970
I wonder if that son-of-a-gun
made it all right.

304
00:31:58,380 --> 00:32:00,130
What's that windmill?

305
00:32:00,130 --> 00:32:03,710
According to Gustav,
it brings water up into the castle, sir.

306
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:07,300
Where does that water come out?

307
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:08,760
A fountain in the battery up above, sir.

308
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:10,010
- Come with me!
- Yes, sir!

309
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:40,170
Inspector! Paris Headquarters has ordered
our withdrawal. We are to return at once.

310
00:32:40,540 --> 00:32:43,960
What?! What preposterous
nonsense is this?! I'm verifying this!

311
00:32:57,770 --> 00:32:59,730
What did you say?!
Lupin's advance notice...

312
00:32:59,730 --> 00:33:01,230
So, the justification was...

313
00:33:01,230 --> 00:33:03,360
Hm? The Count?

314
00:33:04,270 --> 00:33:06,360
Police officers are
not bootlicking lackeys!

315
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:08,400
Whether he likes it or not...

316
00:33:08,780 --> 00:33:09,700
Hello?

317
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:10,780
Hello?!

318
00:33:10,990 --> 00:33:12,950
Dammit...

319
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:15,080
I'm taking this up with the Count!

320
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:21,710
And there's your personal
guide to the Count.

321
00:33:26,090 --> 00:33:27,880
I want to see the Count immediately.

322
00:33:28,130 --> 00:33:30,050
Did you hear me?! Let me through!

323
00:33:30,050 --> 00:33:31,340
Give it up.

324
00:33:32,550 --> 00:33:35,890
Only those deemed trustworthy
are permitted beyond this point.

325
00:33:36,430 --> 00:33:39,480
What?! Are you saying that
the ICPO can't be trusted?!

326
00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:43,440
I believe you have been ordered to
withdraw. Please take your leave.

327
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:46,730
H-How did you know about that?

328
00:33:46,730 --> 00:33:49,530
We can deal with the likes of Lupin
without the help of you Orientals.

329
00:33:49,530 --> 00:33:50,780
Now, leave.

330
00:33:53,450 --> 00:33:55,160
I see. I understand.

331
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:56,330
We'll pull out for now.

332
00:33:56,330 --> 00:33:56,950
Yes, sir.

333
00:34:09,460 --> 00:34:11,090
Did you just see me come here?!

334
00:34:11,090 --> 00:34:11,630
What?

335
00:34:11,630 --> 00:34:13,430
You blithering idiot! That was Lupin!

336
00:34:13,430 --> 00:34:15,100
He disguised himself
as me and got inside!

337
00:34:15,100 --> 00:34:17,600
All that brawn and you can't
even see through a disguise?!

338
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:19,390
- You good-for-nothing!
- Darn it!

339
00:34:19,720 --> 00:34:21,520
Follow me!

340
00:34:21,890 --> 00:34:24,400
Don't let Lupin get away!

341
00:34:30,820 --> 00:34:32,110
Stop right there!

342
00:34:33,410 --> 00:34:34,610
Lupin!

343
00:34:34,740 --> 00:34:35,700
Lupin?!

344
00:34:37,620 --> 00:34:40,160
Stop this! Lupin is... Lupin is...

345
00:34:40,750 --> 00:34:41,960
Help the Inspector!

346
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:43,620
Attack!

347
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:51,720
Wow, look at them going at it!

348
00:34:53,340 --> 00:34:55,300
Stop it! That's Lupin!

349
00:34:55,300 --> 00:34:56,850
Darn it!

350
00:34:58,310 --> 00:34:59,430
Get off my foot!

351
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:16,450
Lupin!

352
00:35:16,700 --> 00:35:17,740
Whoa-oh!

353
00:35:32,710 --> 00:35:34,630
It seems we caught something.

354
00:35:40,010 --> 00:35:42,640
The idiot. He should have
gotten himself out of here.

355
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:43,730
The gendarmes are gone, sir.

356
00:35:43,730 --> 00:35:44,600
Gustav!

357
00:35:44,980 --> 00:35:47,600
Leaving his post?
What is he doing?

358
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:49,940
You stay here.

359
00:35:49,940 --> 00:35:50,570
Yes, sir.

360
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:54,610
Sorry, Pops.

361
00:35:56,530 --> 00:35:59,530
You fool!
Call off this insanity at once!

362
00:35:59,530 --> 00:36:00,740
Do you not see?!

363
00:36:00,740 --> 00:36:03,240
You fell for Lupin's ruse,
hook, line, and sinker!

364
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:04,700
Darn it!

365
00:36:09,330 --> 00:36:11,540
Hey! Let go! Let go!

366
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:21,300
So, that Lupin finally made his way in.

367
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:23,220
I have no words to express my shame.

368
00:36:23,850 --> 00:36:27,190
Tell the police force that their
inspector went ahead and left.

369
00:36:27,690 --> 00:36:30,150
Mysterious disappearances
en route happen all the time.

370
00:36:30,150 --> 00:36:30,980
Yes, sir.

371
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:56,720
Don't move.

372
00:36:58,340 --> 00:37:00,140
Good evening, Fujicakes.

373
00:37:00,140 --> 00:37:01,090
Lupin!

374
00:37:01,090 --> 00:37:04,390
A woman engrossed in her
work is a beautiful sight.

375
00:37:04,390 --> 00:37:06,430
You've gotten this far inside already?

376
00:37:06,430 --> 00:37:09,440
We haven't seen each other
in a year and that's all I get?

377
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:11,480
I searched high and low, you know.

378
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:12,520
Lupin...

379
00:37:12,520 --> 00:37:15,150
What you're searching for
is where the bride is, right?

380
00:37:15,530 --> 00:37:17,440
Oh, you knew?

381
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:20,990
I don't mind telling you, but promise
you won't get in the way of my work?

382
00:37:20,990 --> 00:37:23,580
I won't, I won't! I never have!

383
00:37:23,580 --> 00:37:24,830
I don't know about that.

384
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:27,040
The top of the tower on the north side.

385
00:37:27,040 --> 00:37:29,830
Though, I imagine it'll be
impossible for you to get in.

386
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:35,000
Lupin...

387
00:38:00,650 --> 00:38:03,530
Dang. What an awful place
to lock someone up.

388
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:23,950
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

389
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:36,750
Got i– Wha?

390
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:38,420
Whoa, whoa!

391
00:39:38,420 --> 00:39:40,500
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

392
00:39:40,880 --> 00:39:46,890
Aaaaaaaah!

393
00:41:02,210 --> 00:41:03,210
Who are you?

394
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:05,170
I am a thief.

395
00:41:06,170 --> 00:41:07,590
A thief, sir?

396
00:41:11,930 --> 00:41:14,260
Good evening, Miss Bride.

397
00:41:15,310 --> 00:41:17,480
You are that man
from earlier, aren't you?

398
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:19,310
You forgot this.

399
00:41:22,190 --> 00:41:23,150
My!

400
00:41:23,150 --> 00:41:24,820
You came all this way just for this?

401
00:41:24,820 --> 00:41:27,240
When you would be killed if
the Count were to find you?

402
00:41:27,240 --> 00:41:31,360
Oh, but it is in the nature of a
thief to target and be targeted.

403
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:33,740
I will leave once the job is done.

404
00:41:33,950 --> 00:41:35,120
The job?

405
00:41:36,450 --> 00:41:39,830
If only there were something
I could offer you, but...

406
00:41:40,330 --> 00:41:42,170
I am a captive right now.

407
00:41:42,170 --> 00:41:43,000
Oh...

408
00:41:44,290 --> 00:41:45,420
Take this.

409
00:41:49,050 --> 00:41:50,380
My target is a treasure

410
00:41:50,380 --> 00:41:55,220
that an evil sorcerer locked
away at the top of a tall tower.

411
00:41:58,350 --> 00:42:02,310
Please allow yourself to be
stolen away by this thief.

412
00:42:02,310 --> 00:42:03,730
Me?

413
00:42:07,030 --> 00:42:10,280
Rescuing jewels held prisoner in safes...

414
00:42:10,780 --> 00:42:13,950
And releasing girls about
to be forced into marriage

415
00:42:13,950 --> 00:42:16,490
to run free in green fields...

416
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:20,910
These are all jobs for a thief.

417
00:42:22,170 --> 00:42:24,380
You would give me my freedom?

418
00:42:39,100 --> 00:42:40,140
Thank you.

419
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:41,560
I really appreciate it.

420
00:42:42,390 --> 00:42:46,270
But you do not know just how
terrible the House of Cagliostro is.

421
00:42:49,150 --> 00:42:51,070
Please, just leave.

422
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,790
Oh, how could this be?

423
00:43:00,790 --> 00:43:04,370
The girl believes in
the evil sorcerer's powers,

424
00:43:04,370 --> 00:43:07,380
and yet, she would not try
to believe in the thief's powers.

425
00:43:07,380 --> 00:43:09,550
If the girl would only believe,

426
00:43:09,550 --> 00:43:11,710
the thief would be
capable of flying the skies

427
00:43:11,710 --> 00:43:15,760
or even drinking the lake dry!

428
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:41,160
My!

429
00:43:41,490 --> 00:43:43,870
Right now, this is the best he can do.

430
00:44:18,360 --> 00:44:19,700
Sir Thief!

431
00:44:20,490 --> 00:44:23,790
Hey! Treat the lady with more respect!

432
00:44:34,130 --> 00:44:37,880
Thank you for coming all this way
to deliver the ring, my dear Lupin.

433
00:44:37,880 --> 00:44:41,350
I'm deeply touched by
the grand welcome, Count.

434
00:44:41,350 --> 00:44:44,270
I hate to get right to it, but I'm
going to have you go away now.

435
00:44:44,270 --> 00:44:47,390
Oh, but will you be able
to get rid of me so easily?

436
00:44:47,770 --> 00:44:50,150
N-No! You must not injure that man!

437
00:44:50,150 --> 00:44:53,860
It'll be okay, missy. You have to
have faith in the thief's powers.

438
00:44:56,070 --> 00:44:57,320
Monsieur!

439
00:44:57,320 --> 00:45:00,030
Yes! The Monsieur is here!

440
00:45:00,030 --> 00:45:02,280
He'll be right back, okay?

441
00:45:03,830 --> 00:45:06,000
Now, what's the game going to be?

442
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:08,460
It would be easy to tear you apart,

443
00:45:08,460 --> 00:45:11,000
but I hardly think we need
to sully the bride's room

444
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:12,500
with the blood of a petty thief.

445
00:45:12,500 --> 00:45:14,380
You say that now...

446
00:45:14,380 --> 00:45:16,210
You'll regret it later.

447
00:45:16,460 --> 00:45:18,930
That will be the last
of your smart retorts.

448
00:45:26,180 --> 00:45:30,480
That hole leads to a hell that
no one has ever crawled out of.

449
00:46:00,590 --> 00:46:04,300
You look so sweet, and yet, you've
already attracted a man to your side.

450
00:46:04,300 --> 00:46:06,970
The Cagliostro blood
always comes through.

451
00:46:08,520 --> 00:46:10,690
You are worthy of becoming my wife.

452
00:46:10,690 --> 00:46:13,520
Murderer. You are not human.

453
00:46:13,520 --> 00:46:16,820
Why, yes, my hands are covered in blood.

454
00:46:16,820 --> 00:46:19,030
But so are yours.

455
00:46:19,030 --> 00:46:20,530
Generation after generation,

456
00:46:20,530 --> 00:46:23,320
my family has served as
the shadow to your family,

457
00:46:23,320 --> 00:46:26,950
overseeing schemes and
assassinations to support this country.

458
00:46:26,950 --> 00:46:28,660
Let go of me! You disgust me!

459
00:46:31,830 --> 00:46:34,380
I won't have you telling me
that you didn't know.

460
00:46:35,080 --> 00:46:37,880
You are of Cagliostro as well.

461
00:46:37,880 --> 00:46:42,340
The same ancient blood of the Goths
that flows in my veins flows in yours.

462
00:46:45,340 --> 00:46:48,560
Clarisse, after four hundred long years,

463
00:46:48,560 --> 00:46:52,440
light and shadow, the two houses of
Cagliostro that have been divided,

464
00:46:52,440 --> 00:46:55,270
are now about to become as one.

465
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:56,520
Take a look.

466
00:46:56,940 --> 00:46:59,650
This is the gold goat that has
been passed down in my family.

467
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:00,860
When your...

468
00:47:01,610 --> 00:47:05,030
...ring with the silver goat comes
together to become one with it,

469
00:47:05,030 --> 00:47:07,780
the hidden treasure of our
ancestors will be restored.

470
00:47:07,780 --> 00:47:10,080
Ooh, I heard that!
I totally heard that!

471
00:47:10,080 --> 00:47:12,080
A marriage for treasure!

472
00:47:12,080 --> 00:47:14,080
- It's him!
- The counterfeit bill printer Count!

473
00:47:14,080 --> 00:47:17,290
Everything he says and does is a sham!

474
00:47:17,290 --> 00:47:20,420
The girl is a very kindhearted,
wonderful young lady.

475
00:47:22,630 --> 00:47:23,800
Monsieur? Monsieur?

476
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:25,720
Yes! He's alive and well!

477
00:47:25,720 --> 00:47:29,390
Thanks to the girl believing in him,
he can even fly the skies.

478
00:47:29,390 --> 00:47:33,020
Sir Thief will come and steal you
away for sure, so you just wait.

479
00:47:33,020 --> 00:47:33,850
I will.

480
00:47:34,350 --> 00:47:36,310
Blast it! So it's that ring?!

481
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:37,810
Give it here!

482
00:47:39,770 --> 00:47:41,690
Hey, Count, you listen
and you listen good!

483
00:47:43,110 --> 00:47:44,820
I've got the real ring!

484
00:47:44,820 --> 00:47:46,530
You try and lay a finger on that girl,

485
00:47:46,530 --> 00:47:48,410
and here's what I'll
do to your precious ring!

486
00:47:50,990 --> 00:47:52,290
It was a fake!

487
00:48:03,510 --> 00:48:04,840
Well, crap!

488
00:48:05,170 --> 00:48:08,800
Treat me like bodily wastes, will you?!
Well, pooh-pooh to that!

489
00:48:09,050 --> 00:48:10,260
- Did he fall?
- Probably.

490
00:48:10,260 --> 00:48:11,220
Make sure.

491
00:48:11,220 --> 00:48:14,230
That is not a place fit
for the living to visit.

492
00:48:14,230 --> 00:48:16,520
He is certain to die if
we leave him down there.

493
00:48:16,520 --> 00:48:18,600
The weasel has the ring.

494
00:48:18,980 --> 00:48:20,440
As you wish, sir.

495
00:48:20,860 --> 00:48:21,980
You just wait!

496
00:48:21,980 --> 00:48:24,900
I'll tear that petty
thief of yours to shreds!

497
00:49:41,310 --> 00:49:44,320
Four hundred years of
killing and more killing...

498
00:49:44,320 --> 00:49:46,190
May you rest in peace.

499
00:50:12,010 --> 00:50:12,890
Lupin!

500
00:50:13,180 --> 00:50:15,550
Why, you! Surrender quietly!

501
00:50:15,800 --> 00:50:17,720
Pops, I'm amazed you're all right.

502
00:50:17,720 --> 00:50:20,480
Tell me! Where's the exit?!
Where'd you come in from?!

503
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:22,350
I got the shaft, too.

504
00:50:22,350 --> 00:50:23,150
What?

505
00:50:25,860 --> 00:50:28,780
By the looks of it, you've
been walking for quite a while.

506
00:50:28,780 --> 00:50:31,700
Shut up! I won't take pity from a thief!

507
00:50:31,700 --> 00:50:35,200
Well, let's kick back and relax.
There's no way out anyway.

508
00:50:36,200 --> 00:50:37,950
Make a little room for me there, will you?

509
00:50:39,540 --> 00:50:41,960
Pops, mind lending me a light?

510
00:50:41,960 --> 00:50:44,790
Lupin, what in the world is the deal
with this horde of dead bodies?

511
00:50:44,790 --> 00:50:46,750
It doesn't strike me as a gravesite.

512
00:50:46,750 --> 00:50:48,590
Take a look at the wall there.

513
00:50:56,100 --> 00:50:57,760
Th-This is...

514
00:51:00,140 --> 00:51:02,270
May you rest in peace.

515
00:51:04,230 --> 00:51:06,440
I'd figured this was no ordinary castle,

516
00:51:06,440 --> 00:51:09,280
but a secret worth
going this far to keep...

517
00:51:09,440 --> 00:51:11,400
Hey, is that what you're after, too?

518
00:51:11,900 --> 00:51:13,740
The one who's up to that is Fujicakes.

519
00:51:13,740 --> 00:51:16,450
I just hope she doesn't end
up joining the dearly departed.

520
00:51:16,910 --> 00:51:19,240
Anyway, making a fuss isn't
going to get us anywhere.

521
00:51:19,240 --> 00:51:21,750
G'night, Pops.

522
00:51:36,090 --> 00:51:37,800
Man, it's cold.

523
00:51:37,800 --> 00:51:39,640
Wow, look at the time.

524
00:51:39,640 --> 00:51:41,140
How do things look?

525
00:51:41,140 --> 00:51:42,640
No movement yet.

526
00:51:44,440 --> 00:51:46,600
Guess we'll just have to wait.

527
00:52:42,030 --> 00:52:43,870
Gwahahahaha...

528
00:52:43,870 --> 00:52:45,080
Take that!

529
00:52:46,460 --> 00:52:47,210
Hup!

530
00:53:24,160 --> 00:53:25,620
They're taking too long.

531
00:53:27,000 --> 00:53:28,210
Master Jodot!

532
00:53:31,380 --> 00:53:33,210
Ah! Well done!

533
00:53:37,590 --> 00:53:38,920
And, heave!

534
00:53:42,340 --> 00:53:44,180
Curse you, Lupin!

535
00:53:51,350 --> 00:53:52,860
This is a coffin!

536
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:56,690
Huh? Wha?

537
00:54:02,990 --> 00:54:04,780
What the heck is this place?

538
00:54:16,800 --> 00:54:18,630
These are 10,000-yen bills!

539
00:54:18,630 --> 00:54:20,840
Goodness! And so are all these?!

540
00:54:22,890 --> 00:54:25,100
These are sure well-made.

541
00:54:25,260 --> 00:54:26,970
Pops, take a look.

542
00:54:28,100 --> 00:54:29,850
West German 1000-mark bills!

543
00:54:29,850 --> 00:54:31,810
Pounds. Dollars.

544
00:54:31,810 --> 00:54:35,270
Francs! Rubles! Rupees!
Pesos! Crowns! Liras!

545
00:54:35,980 --> 00:54:38,230
Whoa! There's even won!

546
00:54:38,230 --> 00:54:39,900
They've got the whole world covered.

547
00:54:41,200 --> 00:54:43,410
P-Printing counterfeit bills!

548
00:54:43,530 --> 00:54:46,370
Lupin, so this is the castle's secret?!

549
00:54:46,370 --> 00:54:47,120
That's right.

550
00:54:47,120 --> 00:54:51,960
Gothic bills were once hailed as being superior
to even the real thing and this is the heart of it all.

551
00:54:52,500 --> 00:54:57,380
Fake currency has played a shadowy part in
every upheaval in Europe since the Middle Ages.

552
00:54:57,630 --> 00:55:01,630
It brought down the Bourbon Dynasty by
serving as a source of funds for Napoleon.

553
00:55:02,130 --> 00:55:06,640
And in 1927, it also
triggered the Great Depression.

554
00:55:07,350 --> 00:55:11,350
The key player of the black hole behind
the scenes of history, the Gothic bill.

555
00:55:11,680 --> 00:55:13,810
And of those who tried to
get a peek at its source,

556
00:55:13,810 --> 00:55:15,770
not a soul ever made it back out.

557
00:55:18,570 --> 00:55:20,480
I'd heard the rumors,

558
00:55:20,480 --> 00:55:23,700
but I never imagined that a
sovereign nation was behind it.

559
00:55:24,110 --> 00:55:25,320
What'll you do, Pops?

560
00:55:25,320 --> 00:55:28,120
Now that you've seen it,
there's no going back.

561
00:55:28,120 --> 00:55:31,200
I know that. The police officer in
me is itching to get on the case.

562
00:55:32,040 --> 00:55:35,040
Temporary truce
until we get out of here?

563
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:38,250
Fine. But I won't aid a thief.

564
00:55:38,250 --> 00:55:41,590
Once we've escaped,
I'll arrest you without fail.

565
00:55:41,590 --> 00:55:42,880
Fantastic.

566
00:55:42,880 --> 00:55:43,840
Okay, then...

567
00:55:43,840 --> 00:55:45,180
Let's shake on it!

568
00:55:47,220 --> 00:55:48,640
I won't collude with you.

569
00:55:48,640 --> 00:55:49,680
Well, now.

570
00:55:57,560 --> 00:55:58,270
Miss Fujiko.

571
00:55:58,270 --> 00:56:00,940
I saw my opportunity,
so I've come to say goodbye.

572
00:56:02,940 --> 00:56:04,440
What in the world are you...

573
00:56:04,780 --> 00:56:07,530
Hired as the Lady
Clarisse's personal servant,

574
00:56:07,530 --> 00:56:09,620
the one and only
woman inside the castle...

575
00:56:09,830 --> 00:56:11,240
But the truth is,

576
00:56:11,240 --> 00:56:14,200
I'm a female spy who came to
delve into this castle's secrets.

577
00:56:14,450 --> 00:56:17,580
I was planning on sticking around a
little longer, but Lupin came, right?

578
00:56:17,580 --> 00:56:19,840
It's going to become messy, so I'm leaving.

579
00:56:20,380 --> 00:56:22,210
You know that gentleman?

580
00:56:22,210 --> 00:56:24,090
Better than I wish I ever did.

581
00:56:24,510 --> 00:56:26,970
Allies at times and enemies at others.

582
00:56:26,970 --> 00:56:29,260
I suppose we might've been
lovers at one point, too.

583
00:56:29,890 --> 00:56:32,810
He's a born womanizer.
Be careful.

584
00:56:33,060 --> 00:56:34,350
He left you?

585
00:56:34,350 --> 00:56:35,810
Certainly not.

586
00:56:35,810 --> 00:56:37,230
I left him.

587
00:56:41,230 --> 00:56:43,150
Smoke coming from the pitfall!

588
00:56:43,150 --> 00:56:44,150
A fire...

589
00:56:47,400 --> 00:56:48,860
It's coming from the basement.

590
00:56:51,700 --> 00:56:52,490
Movement!

591
00:56:52,490 --> 00:56:53,790
So, he's kicked things off!

592
00:57:07,050 --> 00:57:09,840
Bad news, sir! The fire's origin is
believed to be the basement workshop!

593
00:57:09,840 --> 00:57:11,220
What?! Put it out right away!

594
00:57:11,220 --> 00:57:11,930
Yes, sir!

595
00:57:11,930 --> 00:57:13,310
Darn you! Shut that thing!

596
00:57:13,310 --> 00:57:14,640
You all go, too!

597
00:57:15,890 --> 00:57:18,100
Blasted Jodot.
Don't tell me he failed...

598
00:57:23,900 --> 00:57:26,900
Pops, hurry it up!
We're going to have visitors soon!

599
00:57:26,900 --> 00:57:29,490
Proof! I need proof!

600
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:37,000
Curse you, Lupin!

601
00:57:39,250 --> 00:57:42,130
Find him!
He should still be in here!

602
00:57:45,840 --> 00:57:48,170
Don't let it scare you!
Get to it!

603
00:57:53,470 --> 00:57:55,260
There's Lupin! After him!

604
00:57:55,260 --> 00:57:56,850
You put the fire out!

605
00:58:04,690 --> 00:58:05,900
It's the chapel!

606
00:58:12,610 --> 00:58:13,240
Monsieur!

607
00:58:13,240 --> 00:58:14,910
Lupin! And Zenigata, too?!

608
00:58:22,250 --> 00:58:24,210
They mean to steal the autogyro.

609
00:58:27,920 --> 00:58:28,800
You fool!

610
00:58:28,800 --> 00:58:31,800
I will take my reprimand later.
He is going after the Lady Clarisse!

611
00:58:31,800 --> 00:58:33,010
Please hurry!

612
00:58:40,730 --> 00:58:42,100
Hurry up!

613
00:58:50,530 --> 00:58:52,320
Darn it! Don't underestimate
the Metropolitan Police!

614
00:58:52,320 --> 00:58:53,570
Pops, get on!

615
00:59:03,670 --> 00:59:05,130
So long!

616
00:59:05,130 --> 00:59:07,460
Pops, I'm going to
make a quick pit stop.

617
00:59:07,460 --> 00:59:09,420
If this is a kidnapping for
ransom, I won't cooperate.

618
00:59:09,420 --> 00:59:11,130
It's a non-business venture.

619
00:59:17,470 --> 00:59:18,680
He's coming this way.

620
00:59:37,820 --> 00:59:39,200
It's bulletproof glass!

621
00:59:40,910 --> 00:59:43,620
We can't open this!
Please, don't mind me and just go!

622
00:59:53,300 --> 00:59:54,630
Pops, take the wheel.

623
00:59:54,630 --> 00:59:57,970
Wh-Wh-What?! Hey, w-wait,
Lupin, I've never done this!

624
00:59:58,640 --> 01:00:00,680
Whee! And here we are.

625
01:00:02,140 --> 01:00:03,350
Clarisse?

626
01:00:03,560 --> 01:00:04,680
Monsieur!

627
01:00:04,680 --> 01:00:07,480
I have come to take you away!
Fujiko, rope!

628
01:00:07,480 --> 01:00:09,150
Don't order me around!

629
01:00:16,740 --> 01:00:17,610
Miss Fujiko!

630
01:00:19,370 --> 01:00:20,330
Go, quick!

631
01:00:33,670 --> 01:00:34,380
Monsieur!

632
01:00:34,380 --> 01:00:36,170
Okay, you're safe now.

633
01:00:41,180 --> 01:00:43,270
Pops, over here!
Here, here, here!

634
01:00:43,270 --> 01:00:46,270
Like it's that easy,
you blithering idiot!

635
01:00:51,400 --> 01:00:52,860
All right, that's good!

636
01:00:54,110 --> 01:00:55,360
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

637
01:00:55,820 --> 01:00:57,530
Hup, hup, hup, hup...

638
01:01:15,840 --> 01:01:16,920
Lupin!

639
01:01:19,220 --> 01:01:21,340
Don't move, you she-rat!

640
01:01:25,520 --> 01:01:29,390
Fujiko, I have a lot of
questions to put to you later.

641
01:01:29,390 --> 01:01:31,400
Jodot, finish Lupin.

642
01:01:31,400 --> 01:01:32,230
Yes, sir.

643
01:01:32,230 --> 01:01:33,860
No! You mustn't shoot him!

644
01:01:33,860 --> 01:01:36,610
If you mean to kill him,
then I will die, too!

645
01:01:36,610 --> 01:01:37,530
Fire.

646
01:01:57,460 --> 01:02:00,550
Your attitude is commendable, Clarisse.

647
01:02:04,760 --> 01:02:07,140
Get the ring back and come here.

648
01:02:07,770 --> 01:02:10,980
If you become my wife,
I'll spare Lupin's life.

649
01:02:11,730 --> 01:02:14,060
Or you can both die now.

650
01:02:14,060 --> 01:02:16,070
I'll let you choose as you will.

651
01:02:26,580 --> 01:02:28,410
Monsieur, the ring...

652
01:02:29,040 --> 01:02:31,210
No, Clarisse.

653
01:02:31,620 --> 01:02:33,040
You can't...

654
01:02:33,040 --> 01:02:36,040
Under his collar.
Lupin always hides things there.

655
01:02:36,420 --> 01:02:39,050
Damn you, Fujiko...

656
01:02:51,690 --> 01:02:52,640
Here is the ring.

657
01:02:52,640 --> 01:02:56,650
Spare this man and Miss Fujiko, or
else I will simply throw it in the lake.

658
01:02:56,940 --> 01:03:00,610
Trust me. Put it on your finger
and come over here.

659
01:03:00,610 --> 01:03:01,780
Shall I fire?

660
01:03:01,780 --> 01:03:03,450
Wait until the ring gets here.

661
01:03:13,500 --> 01:03:14,960
Lupin!

662
01:03:18,800 --> 01:03:20,380
Shoot them!
Don't let them get away!

663
01:03:25,340 --> 01:03:27,640
You dirty coward!
You said you would spare them!

664
01:03:28,640 --> 01:03:32,230
They'd seen the basement workshop.
You thought I'd let them leave alive?!

665
01:03:38,860 --> 01:03:40,860
I finally have it in my hands!

666
01:03:57,080 --> 01:03:59,540
Lupin, we'll say you
owe me one for today.

667
01:03:59,540 --> 01:04:00,590
Later.

668
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:09,680
And now, we retreat
without seeing any action?!

669
01:04:14,430 --> 01:04:16,440
Augh, we can't go much longer!

670
01:04:16,440 --> 01:04:17,650
Jump down!

671
01:04:30,490 --> 01:04:33,330
Yet again I have cut a worthless object.

672
01:04:34,750 --> 01:04:38,330
Lupin, you better not kick the
bucket before I catch you!

673
01:04:41,920 --> 01:04:44,130
Whatever the case,
this is certainly a problem.

674
01:04:44,130 --> 01:04:45,720
A dark plot is what this is.

675
01:04:49,390 --> 01:04:51,430
Please order me to move against them!

676
01:04:51,430 --> 01:04:53,640
We have all this indisputable evidence!

677
01:04:53,640 --> 01:04:55,020
I saw it myself!

678
01:04:55,020 --> 01:04:57,480
A whole row of
state-of-the-art printing presses...

679
01:04:57,480 --> 01:04:59,400
I know that!

680
01:05:01,150 --> 01:05:03,860
This is a highly political problem.

681
01:05:03,860 --> 01:05:07,650
Our jurisdiction here at Interpol
is limited to international crimes.

682
01:05:07,650 --> 01:05:10,410
Secretary General,
it is clear that this is criminal!

683
01:05:10,410 --> 01:05:12,160
You just don't get it.

684
01:05:12,160 --> 01:05:14,490
We're talking about a sovereign
state and a member of the UN.

685
01:05:14,490 --> 01:05:17,790
Even Interpol cannot conduct
a compulsory investigation.

686
01:05:17,790 --> 01:05:20,630
Not only that, but the situation is
exceedingly unfavorable for us.

687
01:05:20,630 --> 01:05:24,750
Did you see this photo that's on the front
page of every newspaper around the world?

688
01:05:24,960 --> 01:05:27,920
The bravery of the Count,
who personally protected his bride.

689
01:05:27,920 --> 01:05:30,300
"Lupin Fails to Abduct Princess Clarisse".

690
01:05:30,300 --> 01:05:33,560
They also say, "Lupin's Accomplice
Disguised As Zenigata".

691
01:05:33,560 --> 01:05:35,640
That was all me, the real McCoy.

692
01:05:35,640 --> 01:05:39,100
That's problematic. As an active duty
police officer, that was imprudent of you.

693
01:05:39,100 --> 01:05:41,690
I believe I reported
what really happened!

694
01:05:41,940 --> 01:05:45,570
The issue here is which
side the public will believe.

695
01:05:45,570 --> 01:05:47,150
We stand no chance, surely.

696
01:05:47,150 --> 01:05:50,660
The Count supposedly has a lot
of political friends in the West.

697
01:05:50,660 --> 01:05:53,870
I imagine many countries would have
a problem if the truth were revealed.

698
01:05:53,870 --> 01:05:56,410
Exactly! In point of fact,
there's proof that a certain country

699
01:05:56,410 --> 01:05:59,040
ordered a massive quantity
of counterfeit US dollar bills!

700
01:05:59,040 --> 01:06:01,370
Humph! And these fake rubles
weren't ordered by your CIA?!

701
01:06:01,370 --> 01:06:02,040
What?!

702
01:06:02,040 --> 01:06:03,170
- Stop this!
- How dare you?!

703
01:06:03,170 --> 01:06:05,800
You can't be bringing up
international disputes here!

704
01:06:05,800 --> 01:06:08,210
Precisely! We have no choice
but to have each country

705
01:06:08,210 --> 01:06:10,800
come up with their own
countermeasures for the Gothic bills.

706
01:06:17,310 --> 01:06:19,520
Inspector, we are prepared to mobilize.

707
01:06:19,520 --> 01:06:22,230
We can depart for the Principality
of Cagliostro at any time.

708
01:06:23,520 --> 01:06:24,730
We won't be mobilizing.

709
01:06:24,730 --> 01:06:25,270
Sir?

710
01:06:25,270 --> 01:06:29,650
We'll be off the Lupin case as soon
as they find someone to replace us.

711
01:06:30,030 --> 01:06:32,160
Everyone, prepare to return to Japan.

712
01:06:42,790 --> 01:06:43,830
It's me.

713
01:06:45,340 --> 01:06:46,380
Here's some food.

714
01:06:46,380 --> 01:06:47,590
Much appreciated.

715
01:06:47,590 --> 01:06:48,760
How is he?

716
01:06:48,760 --> 01:06:50,880
His fever seems to have gone down.

717
01:06:51,130 --> 01:06:53,130
It's thanks to you operating on him.

718
01:06:53,380 --> 01:06:55,550
If you want to thank someone,
thank that dog.

719
01:06:56,220 --> 01:06:58,140
That old dog is friendly to no one,

720
01:06:58,140 --> 01:07:00,520
but he won't budge from that man's side.

721
01:07:00,930 --> 01:07:04,600
Otherwise, I probably wouldn't
have offered you folks shelter.

722
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:16,070
Hey, Karl.

723
01:07:16,070 --> 01:07:17,530
He's awake!

724
01:07:18,370 --> 01:07:20,290
Lupin, how're your wounds?

725
01:07:22,460 --> 01:07:25,670
Jigen. Goemon. Long time no see.

726
01:07:25,670 --> 01:07:28,170
Long time? What're you saying?

727
01:07:28,170 --> 01:07:31,210
His memory is in temporary
disarray due to his injuries.

728
01:07:31,210 --> 01:07:35,180
Karl, you're not with
your mistress today?

729
01:07:36,220 --> 01:07:39,180
How do you know that dog's name?

730
01:07:39,760 --> 01:07:44,230
Other than myself, the only one left to know
him as Karl should be the Lady Clarisse.

731
01:07:44,230 --> 01:07:45,480
Clarisse?

732
01:07:46,100 --> 01:07:50,480
I see, so your mistress' name is Clarisse...

733
01:07:50,900 --> 01:07:52,400
Clarisse...

734
01:07:56,490 --> 01:07:57,280
Lupin.

735
01:07:57,990 --> 01:07:59,700
Jigen, what day is today?!

736
01:07:59,700 --> 01:08:01,370
How many days has it been?!

737
01:08:01,740 --> 01:08:03,290
Th-Th-Three days.

738
01:08:03,290 --> 01:08:05,790
What? Then the ceremony's tomorrow.

739
01:08:05,790 --> 01:08:07,540
No time to be...

740
01:08:07,920 --> 01:08:09,170
Owowowowow...

741
01:08:09,170 --> 01:08:11,630
Come on, don't push it.
You'll reopen your wounds.

742
01:08:11,630 --> 01:08:15,090
Food. Bring me food.

743
01:08:15,090 --> 01:08:16,880
Food? Like rice porridge?

744
01:08:16,880 --> 01:08:20,720
I'm low on blood. Bring me
whatever. Just keep it coming.

745
01:08:20,720 --> 01:08:22,810
Easy for you to say, but...

746
01:08:22,810 --> 01:08:24,560
I'll handle it.

747
01:08:30,230 --> 01:08:32,320
You idiot, quit stuffing yourself like that.

748
01:08:32,320 --> 01:08:33,940
Your stomach won't take it.

749
01:08:34,690 --> 01:08:37,700
Shuddup! Even a jet airplane
can get fixed up in twelve hours!

750
01:08:49,880 --> 01:08:52,300
See? What'd I tell you?
Need a wash basin?

751
01:08:53,170 --> 01:08:53,960
Huh?

752
01:08:53,960 --> 01:08:55,300
What's that?

753
01:08:57,970 --> 01:08:59,890
Says he'll sleep, now that he's eaten.

754
01:09:03,010 --> 01:09:04,640
I had no idea.

755
01:09:04,640 --> 01:09:06,390
All for the Lady Clarisse...

756
01:09:06,390 --> 01:09:09,310
But with Lupin in this shape...

757
01:09:09,310 --> 01:09:12,820
It sounds as though you have a great
deal of history with the Lady Clarisse.

758
01:09:13,020 --> 01:09:15,570
I used to be the palace groundskeeper.

759
01:09:16,190 --> 01:09:19,070
The Lady Clarisse loved
plants as a child.

760
01:09:19,240 --> 01:09:23,240
When the Prince and his wife passed
away and she was to enter the convent,

761
01:09:23,240 --> 01:09:25,750
she entrusted this dog to me.

762
01:09:25,750 --> 01:09:30,210
So, he sniffed out the
Princess' scent on Lupin.

763
01:09:30,830 --> 01:09:34,130
How did this man know the dog's name?

764
01:09:34,420 --> 01:09:37,510
Who knows? This guy's
constantly falling in love, so...

765
01:09:37,760 --> 01:09:39,090
It's nothing like that.

766
01:09:39,090 --> 01:09:40,800
You were awake?

767
01:09:41,890 --> 01:09:44,260
It was over ten years ago now.

768
01:09:45,220 --> 01:09:49,560
I was a greenhorn, eager to set
out and make a name for myself.

769
01:09:57,740 --> 01:09:59,650
I did crazy things,

770
01:09:59,650 --> 01:10:01,320
and after making a real show of myself,

771
01:10:01,320 --> 01:10:03,320
in the end, I went after the Gothic bills.

772
01:10:12,920 --> 01:10:17,300
I managed to pull myself up onto the shore
somehow, but I couldn't budge another inch.

773
01:10:22,340 --> 01:10:24,470
Karl? What's wrong, Karl?

774
01:10:33,980 --> 01:10:36,980
Looks like my time's
come to pay the piper.

775
01:10:42,360 --> 01:10:43,450
Water...

776
01:10:55,710 --> 01:10:58,050
She helped me drink the water,
her hands shaking...

777
01:10:58,050 --> 01:11:01,880
And shining on her finger was that ring.

778
01:11:02,800 --> 01:11:04,510
I'm ashamed to say,

779
01:11:04,510 --> 01:11:07,350
I'd totally forgotten about it
until I saw the ring again.

780
01:11:15,690 --> 01:11:17,110
That's Fujiko's motorbike.

781
01:11:17,900 --> 01:11:19,650
It's a clipping from today's newspaper.

782
01:11:19,650 --> 01:11:23,820
It says that tomorrow morning, an archbishop
is coming from the Vatican for the ceremony.

783
01:11:35,080 --> 01:11:37,170
I'm quitting!

784
01:11:37,500 --> 01:11:38,590
Fujiko?!

785
01:11:39,420 --> 01:11:42,420
What?! Lupin's going to hit
the wedding?! Is this true?!

786
01:11:42,420 --> 01:11:43,970
If you're pursuing Lupin,

787
01:11:43,970 --> 01:11:46,260
you have full authority
to mobilize, right?

788
01:11:46,970 --> 01:11:49,850
Right... I hadn't thought of that!

789
01:12:13,120 --> 01:12:15,210
We're in a hurry!
Would you move aside?!

790
01:12:15,210 --> 01:12:18,580
It's no use.
It's completely jammed up ahead.

791
01:12:18,580 --> 01:12:20,960
They said there was a landslide
seven kilometers down the road.

792
01:12:20,960 --> 01:12:23,130
Is there no other way?

793
01:12:23,130 --> 01:12:25,050
We're going to be late.

794
01:12:25,050 --> 01:12:25,760
Right...

795
01:12:25,760 --> 01:12:29,300
By gosh, aren't ya
the fine lord archbishop?

796
01:12:29,300 --> 01:12:31,560
Yep, just like I reckoned.

797
01:12:31,560 --> 01:12:35,140
Would ya be so kind as
to bless this li'I baby goat?

798
01:12:36,600 --> 01:12:38,400
Oh, you're a local, right?

799
01:12:38,400 --> 01:12:41,150
Aren't there any other ways to
get to the Castle of Cagliostro?

800
01:12:41,150 --> 01:12:43,530
If ya don't mind country roads,
there's a way over there.

801
01:12:43,530 --> 01:12:44,780
Thank goodness!

802
01:12:44,780 --> 01:12:45,950
Would you show me the way?

803
01:12:45,950 --> 01:12:47,150
Come on, get in. Get in.

804
01:12:47,320 --> 01:12:51,330
Sure, sure. If it's for the fine
lord archbishop, then sure.

805
01:12:57,210 --> 01:12:58,250
Keep it up, men!

806
01:12:58,250 --> 01:13:00,040
One more hill and
we'll be at the border!

807
01:13:00,040 --> 01:13:02,300
We have to get there
by dusk at the latest!

808
01:13:04,380 --> 01:13:06,800
Heave-ho! Heave-ho!

809
01:13:15,560 --> 01:13:17,180
Is this really all right?

810
01:13:17,180 --> 01:13:19,190
Publicizing this on TV...

811
01:13:19,440 --> 01:13:24,730
His Highness wishes to show the
world that this is a legitimate wedding.

812
01:13:24,730 --> 01:13:28,400
Ah, His Grace, the Archbishop, has arrived.

813
01:13:35,120 --> 01:13:37,160
Do you think Lupin will show up?

814
01:13:37,160 --> 01:13:40,120
My Shadows will guard the bride.

815
01:13:40,120 --> 01:13:42,500
All your men have to
do is guard the gate!

816
01:13:42,500 --> 01:13:43,170
Yes, sir.

817
01:14:45,020 --> 01:14:48,190
The time has come for light
and shadow to become as one.

818
01:14:48,480 --> 01:14:50,360
Come, Clarisse.

819
01:16:17,530 --> 01:16:19,950
The House of Cagliostro is a
noble family of ancient blood.

820
01:16:19,950 --> 01:16:25,290
Bring here the proof that
you are their rightful heirs.

821
01:16:31,340 --> 01:16:33,920
In accordance with the customs of old,

822
01:16:33,920 --> 01:16:37,260
the exchange of rings shall
constitute your marriage vows.

823
01:16:38,050 --> 01:16:41,100
Daughter of the Prince of
the Principality of Cagliostro,

824
01:16:41,310 --> 01:16:44,230
Clarisse de Cagliostro,

825
01:16:44,230 --> 01:16:46,810
do you consent to this marriage?

826
01:16:46,810 --> 01:16:50,360
If you do not object,
then respond with silence.

827
01:17:09,040 --> 01:17:12,040
May God bless you...

828
01:17:12,040 --> 01:17:13,500
I object.

829
01:17:15,380 --> 01:17:19,260
These marriage rites are
profoundly tainted by greed.

830
01:17:32,940 --> 01:17:34,020
This is a curse!

831
01:17:34,020 --> 01:17:35,230
No need to fuss.

832
01:17:35,230 --> 01:17:37,240
So, that accursed rat has appeared.

833
01:17:55,210 --> 01:17:59,430
I have come to speak on behalf of
the dead in the dungeon underground.

834
01:17:59,430 --> 01:18:01,890
I want the bride.

835
01:18:02,180 --> 01:18:03,720
Oh, we cannot carry
out the ceremony now.

836
01:18:03,720 --> 01:18:06,270
Get back. This will be
a fine bit of entertainment.

837
01:18:07,890 --> 01:18:11,690
Clarisse, I've come for you.

838
01:18:16,610 --> 01:18:17,860
It's a monster!

839
01:18:18,240 --> 01:18:19,900
Something incredible has happened!

840
01:18:19,900 --> 01:18:21,820
It's Lupin! Lupin's appeared!

841
01:18:21,820 --> 01:18:23,200
Stop the broadcast!

842
01:18:23,410 --> 01:18:24,910
What are you doing?!

843
01:18:25,200 --> 01:18:26,160
Move out!

844
01:18:29,250 --> 01:18:30,290
Clarisse.

845
01:18:30,750 --> 01:18:31,830
Clarisse.

846
01:18:32,170 --> 01:18:34,960
Poor thing.
You've been drugged, haven't you?

847
01:18:34,960 --> 01:18:38,260
Curse you, Count. You made it
so she couldn't speak, didn't you?

848
01:18:47,140 --> 01:18:50,810
- Monsieur!
- You mustn't. You mustn't get closer.

849
01:18:51,850 --> 01:18:53,400
That was foolish, Lupin!

850
01:18:53,400 --> 01:18:55,110
Take care of those men as well!

851
01:18:57,480 --> 01:18:58,610
Clarisse.

852
01:18:58,610 --> 01:19:00,320
Don't cry, Clarisse.

853
01:19:02,450 --> 01:19:04,910
I'll come to you now.

854
01:19:12,160 --> 01:19:13,620
What's going on here?!

855
01:19:13,620 --> 01:19:16,590
I wonder if this gift
will be to your liking, Count.

856
01:19:16,590 --> 01:19:17,500
Highness!

857
01:19:18,050 --> 01:19:20,260
They're the counterfeit
bills you printed.

858
01:19:20,260 --> 01:19:22,380
Take them as payment for the rings.

859
01:19:23,430 --> 01:19:27,300
Blast it! Find him!
He has to be in here somewhere!

860
01:19:27,300 --> 01:19:27,930
Oh!

861
01:19:29,100 --> 01:19:30,470
I've definitely got them now.

862
01:19:30,470 --> 01:19:31,680
Y-You're...

863
01:19:32,180 --> 01:19:33,140
Lupin!

864
01:19:33,730 --> 01:19:34,980
Monsieur!

865
01:19:35,480 --> 01:19:37,860
Curse you!
Play me for a fool, will you?!

866
01:19:37,860 --> 01:19:41,530
No burning up with jealousy now
or you'll get burned, Lolita-loving Count.

867
01:19:53,580 --> 01:19:54,540
Take that!

868
01:20:07,970 --> 01:20:09,430
Lupin! Lupin! Lupin!

869
01:20:09,430 --> 01:20:11,930
Take that! Ladies and gentlemen,
pardon me for keeping you waiting.

870
01:20:11,930 --> 01:20:13,480
We will now resume our broadcast.

871
01:20:13,480 --> 01:20:15,940
The wedding hall is now in utter chaos!

872
01:20:16,560 --> 01:20:17,560
Well, then... Buh-bye!

873
01:20:17,560 --> 01:20:18,400
Die!

874
01:20:25,990 --> 01:20:27,610
After him!
Don't let him get away!

875
01:20:28,200 --> 01:20:31,490
Lupin has fled! The Count is in
a rage and hot on his heels!

876
01:20:32,200 --> 01:20:34,500
Oh, the police have come storming in!

877
01:20:35,750 --> 01:20:37,620
Lupin is under the altar!

878
01:20:38,040 --> 01:20:40,460
Make a hole! Attack!

879
01:20:42,050 --> 01:20:44,920
Zenigata's men are pushing
hard towards the altar!

880
01:20:44,920 --> 01:20:47,260
Oh, here's the gendarmerie!
In the lead is...

881
01:20:47,590 --> 01:20:48,840
Gendarme Captain Gustav!

882
01:20:48,840 --> 01:20:50,430
Secure our rear!

883
01:20:52,010 --> 01:20:53,560
Why, you!

884
01:20:54,930 --> 01:20:57,690
Give no quarter!
Justice is on our side!

885
01:20:58,440 --> 01:21:00,480
The fighting is truly fierce!

886
01:21:00,480 --> 01:21:03,280
What could possibly
be beneath the altar?

887
01:21:03,650 --> 01:21:06,820
Oh, it's a staircase!
There's a hole leading underground!

888
01:21:06,820 --> 01:21:08,950
Could Lupin be inside that hole?

889
01:21:08,950 --> 01:21:10,740
Let us follow with the camera!

890
01:21:11,740 --> 01:21:13,370
Darn you, Lupin!

891
01:21:14,700 --> 01:21:16,080
Lupin! Lupin!

892
01:21:16,080 --> 01:21:18,040
That idiot! What's he doing?!

893
01:21:18,040 --> 01:21:20,040
He's ignoring his orders!
Call him off!

894
01:21:20,040 --> 01:21:22,500
This is being broadcast via satellite!
It's too late!

895
01:21:23,380 --> 01:21:25,760
Whoa! What the heck is this place?!

896
01:21:25,760 --> 01:21:28,260
This practically looks like
a national minting facility!

897
01:21:28,510 --> 01:21:30,140
What's that over there?

898
01:21:32,430 --> 01:21:34,350
Oh, wow!
These are Japanese bills!

899
01:21:34,350 --> 01:21:35,890
Counterfeit bills!

900
01:21:35,890 --> 01:21:38,020
Talk about hamming it up...

901
01:21:38,020 --> 01:21:39,770
This is an incredible revelation!

902
01:21:39,770 --> 01:21:40,730
Take a look!

903
01:21:40,730 --> 01:21:42,610
It's counterfeit currency
from all over the world!

904
01:21:42,610 --> 01:21:45,610
I've made a terrible discovery
during my pursuit of Lupin!

905
01:21:45,610 --> 01:21:47,030
What should I do?!

906
01:21:59,330 --> 01:22:02,750
First things first, we're getting out of this castle.
I'm counting on you, Jigen. Goemon.

907
01:22:02,750 --> 01:22:04,460
Leave it to us.
We'll hold them off here.

908
01:22:04,460 --> 01:22:05,130
Come on.

909
01:22:10,380 --> 01:22:11,430
Gentlemen.

910
01:22:11,430 --> 01:22:13,100
I beg of you to be careful.

911
01:22:13,100 --> 01:22:14,260
And you, too, Noble Jigen.

912
01:22:14,470 --> 01:22:15,010
Huh?

913
01:22:15,010 --> 01:22:17,220
Please make certain
that you return safely.

914
01:22:17,220 --> 01:22:19,440
I will never forget this
debt of gratitude.

915
01:22:19,440 --> 01:22:21,060
Now, you must go.

916
01:22:23,060 --> 01:22:24,980
Clarisse, hurry.

917
01:22:24,980 --> 01:22:25,860
Coming.

918
01:22:32,070 --> 01:22:34,120
She called me Noble Jigen.

919
01:22:34,120 --> 01:22:35,450
A lovely lady...

920
01:22:41,000 --> 01:22:42,170
Let's get this started!

921
01:22:50,090 --> 01:22:52,970
My steel-cleaving Zantetsuken
feels a bit more keen tonight.

922
01:22:52,970 --> 01:22:55,760
Curse you, Lupin, this isn't over yet!

923
01:22:58,100 --> 01:23:00,180
Leave matters within
the castle to me, sir.

924
01:23:00,180 --> 01:23:00,850
Mm.

925
01:23:19,080 --> 01:23:21,540
- Are your wounds causing you pain?
- Nah, they're nothing.

926
01:23:21,540 --> 01:23:23,290
Now, let's get over this thing.

927
01:23:29,630 --> 01:23:31,970
Two goats facing each other...

928
01:23:37,800 --> 01:23:40,060
There are Gothic letters
carved along the seam.

929
01:23:40,060 --> 01:23:42,850
"Binding light and shadow..."

930
01:23:42,850 --> 01:23:45,060
They're worn down and hard to read.

931
01:23:45,400 --> 01:23:48,150
"Binding light and shadow,
tolling the hours is the goat on high,

932
01:23:48,150 --> 01:23:52,440
into whose eyes, facing the sun,
I bid you place me."

933
01:23:53,360 --> 01:23:57,570
Those words have been passed down in my
family since ancient times. Does that help?

934
01:23:57,870 --> 01:24:00,540
Yes, it helps!
Now I know the answer to the riddle!

935
01:24:02,620 --> 01:24:04,040
It's the Count. Come, this way.

936
01:24:10,380 --> 01:24:13,420
They're going inside the machine room
of the clock tower! Moor the boat!

937
01:24:27,900 --> 01:24:29,060
There!

938
01:24:29,360 --> 01:24:31,190
Ooh, here they come.

939
01:24:35,240 --> 01:24:36,700
Hot, hot, hot, hot, hot, hot!

940
01:24:37,860 --> 01:24:38,950
Well, that's no good.

941
01:24:40,370 --> 01:24:41,660
Shut down the lasers.

942
01:24:41,660 --> 01:24:44,250
The idiot. Does he think they
can get out of here?

943
01:25:02,930 --> 01:25:03,850
Scared?

944
01:25:03,850 --> 01:25:04,470
No.

945
01:25:04,470 --> 01:25:05,640
Fantastic!

946
01:25:05,640 --> 01:25:06,480
Here we go!

947
01:25:10,860 --> 01:25:12,070
Don't let him get away!

948
01:25:13,190 --> 01:25:13,900
Oh!

949
01:25:29,420 --> 01:25:30,250
Don't look!

950
01:25:33,130 --> 01:25:34,300
We can't go this way.

951
01:25:34,300 --> 01:25:35,840
You men use the stairs!

952
01:25:35,840 --> 01:25:36,630
Yes, sir!

953
01:25:43,100 --> 01:25:43,850
Oof.

954
01:25:43,850 --> 01:25:45,720
Stay here.
I'm going to block the entrance.

955
01:25:45,720 --> 01:25:46,350
Be careful!

956
01:25:46,350 --> 01:25:47,930
I'll be right back!

957
01:25:59,740 --> 01:26:00,910
There!

958
01:26:22,180 --> 01:26:24,180
Monsieur! Behind you!

959
01:26:26,810 --> 01:26:29,520
Whoops! Hup, hup, hup...

960
01:26:29,520 --> 01:26:31,520
Hey, there, Count!

961
01:26:31,900 --> 01:26:34,560
Accursed rat!
I'll run you through!

962
01:26:34,560 --> 01:26:37,030
Looks like we've come to
the finale at last, Count.

963
01:27:03,090 --> 01:27:04,890
And one more!

964
01:27:06,510 --> 01:27:08,560
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

965
01:27:13,060 --> 01:27:17,150
Hey, Count C,
I dare you to come get me!

966
01:27:18,150 --> 01:27:19,820
Whoops!

967
01:27:20,030 --> 01:27:23,780
Whoa, whoa, whoa... Whoa!
Whoa, whoa, whoa...

968
01:27:25,160 --> 01:27:26,910
Monsieur!

969
01:27:34,790 --> 01:27:37,340
I'll start by taking care of you first!

970
01:27:37,340 --> 01:27:39,170
Clarisse, run!

971
01:27:39,460 --> 01:27:40,710
I'm coming!

972
01:28:07,620 --> 01:28:09,740
How far do you think you're going?

973
01:28:09,740 --> 01:28:11,660
Clarisse...

974
01:28:17,460 --> 01:28:20,750
Come on, come on.
What's wrong?

975
01:28:21,460 --> 01:28:23,670
Not running anymore? Eh?

976
01:28:24,170 --> 01:28:26,890
This will be the end of
the Cagliostro bloodline.

977
01:28:26,890 --> 01:28:27,930
Die, Clarisse.

978
01:28:27,930 --> 01:28:29,180
Wait, Count!

979
01:28:29,180 --> 01:28:30,220
Let's make a deal!

980
01:28:30,930 --> 01:28:34,230
It's too late!
You can watch this woman die!

981
01:28:34,230 --> 01:28:35,520
Listen to what I've got to say.

982
01:28:36,480 --> 01:28:38,810
I'll tell you the secret to these rings.

983
01:28:38,810 --> 01:28:41,690
You can do whatever you
want with the treasure.

984
01:28:41,690 --> 01:28:44,440
But give up on the girl.
Let her go free.

985
01:28:45,070 --> 01:28:47,740
Look at the Capricorn
on the clock face.

986
01:28:47,950 --> 01:28:50,990
That's the goat that faces the
sun and tolls the hours.

987
01:28:50,990 --> 01:28:53,540
It's got two holes in its eyes
to fit the rings into.

988
01:28:54,370 --> 01:28:56,290
I'll let you have these rings,

989
01:28:56,290 --> 01:29:00,340
but if you kill her, I'll throw
them in the lake and I'll kill you.

990
01:29:29,700 --> 01:29:31,320
Ah-ah, that's far enough.

991
01:29:31,320 --> 01:29:32,740
Let Clarisse go inside.

992
01:29:33,660 --> 01:29:36,080
All right, fine.

993
01:29:42,790 --> 01:29:46,800
Lupin, you have to save
your trump cards for the end.

994
01:29:48,380 --> 01:29:49,220
Come!

995
01:29:53,680 --> 01:29:57,060
These are definitely the genuine
articles. The rings are mine now.

996
01:29:57,060 --> 01:29:59,480
Here's your payment
for solving the riddle.

997
01:30:03,860 --> 01:30:05,150
Let go!

998
01:30:05,780 --> 01:30:07,150
Clarisse!

999
01:30:10,660 --> 01:30:11,700
Let go!

1000
01:31:41,870 --> 01:31:42,960
The clock tower!

1001
01:31:54,380 --> 01:31:55,390
Your Highness...

1002
01:32:31,880 --> 01:32:33,170
What the heck is that?

1003
01:33:00,280 --> 01:33:02,990
Cagliostro is done for.

1004
01:33:03,830 --> 01:33:04,950
Cut me down.

1005
01:33:05,410 --> 01:33:07,460
I will not kill needlessly.

1006
01:33:56,970 --> 01:33:57,720
Monsieur...

1007
01:33:57,720 --> 01:33:59,220
Hey, can you stand?

1008
01:33:59,220 --> 01:34:00,300
Take a look.

1009
01:34:23,780 --> 01:34:25,990
The hidden treasure...

1010
01:34:26,660 --> 01:34:30,210
I had no idea there was a
Roman city beneath the lake.

1011
01:34:31,120 --> 01:34:33,290
When the Romans were
driven from this land,

1012
01:34:33,290 --> 01:34:35,500
they built that floodgate
and submerged it.

1013
01:34:35,500 --> 01:34:38,590
And your ancestors
quietly inherited it.

1014
01:34:48,310 --> 01:34:51,140
Truly, a treasure for all mankind.

1015
01:34:51,140 --> 01:34:53,400
It's too big for my pocket.

1016
01:35:11,790 --> 01:35:14,630
So, Interpol got their
lazy bums into gear.

1017
01:35:29,680 --> 01:35:31,350
Will you be leaving?

1018
01:35:31,350 --> 01:35:33,270
Hm? Yeah.

1019
01:35:33,270 --> 01:35:36,360
A lot of scary men
just showed up, so...

1020
01:35:38,940 --> 01:35:43,070
Take me with you. I can't work as
a thief yet, but I'll learn, I promise!

1021
01:35:43,070 --> 01:35:44,990
I... I...

1022
01:35:45,990 --> 01:35:47,200
Please!

1023
01:35:47,200 --> 01:35:48,580
I want to go with you.

1024
01:35:51,830 --> 01:35:53,000
Clarisse.

1025
01:36:02,470 --> 01:36:04,720
Don't give me that silly talk.

1026
01:36:04,720 --> 01:36:06,840
You want to go back
into the darkness again?

1027
01:36:06,840 --> 01:36:09,430
It's taken you this
long to get into the sun.

1028
01:36:09,430 --> 01:36:13,100
Right? Your life is
only getting started here.

1029
01:36:13,100 --> 01:36:16,190
You can't become all grubby like me.

1030
01:36:16,190 --> 01:36:18,900
Oh, yeah! If you ever run into any
trouble, just call any time, okay?

1031
01:36:18,900 --> 01:36:22,490
Monsieur will come running, even if
it's from the other side of the globe.

1032
01:36:32,330 --> 01:36:33,540
Karl!

1033
01:36:34,210 --> 01:36:36,870
Oh, Karl! Karl!

1034
01:36:36,870 --> 01:36:38,040
Lady Clarisse.

1035
01:36:38,040 --> 01:36:39,130
Gramps!

1036
01:36:49,550 --> 01:36:51,470
- Monsieur!
- Toodle-oo!

1037
01:36:52,430 --> 01:36:54,060
Princess!

1038
01:36:56,560 --> 01:36:57,810
Monsieur!

1039
01:36:58,350 --> 01:37:00,320
Clarisse, take care!

1040
01:37:00,520 --> 01:37:01,980
G'bye!

1041
01:37:04,490 --> 01:37:07,910
Thank you, everyone! Goodbye!

1042
01:37:08,070 --> 01:37:09,370
G'bye!

1043
01:37:09,490 --> 01:37:12,330
G'bye!

1044
01:37:24,170 --> 01:37:26,380
Dang it! One step too late!

1045
01:37:26,380 --> 01:37:28,590
That darn Lupin got away with his loot!

1046
01:37:28,590 --> 01:37:31,350
No, that man took nothing.

1047
01:37:31,350 --> 01:37:33,720
He honored me by fighting for my sake.

1048
01:37:33,720 --> 01:37:37,390
No, ma'am, he ran off
with a tremendous prize.

1049
01:37:38,440 --> 01:37:40,310
Your heart.

1050
01:37:42,320 --> 01:37:42,980
Yes.

1051
01:37:44,150 --> 01:37:45,690
Well, then, please excuse me!

1052
01:37:50,950 --> 01:37:53,660
After Lupin! We follow him
to the ends of the earth!

1053
01:38:13,470 --> 01:38:16,350
What a refreshing bunch
of fellows they were.

1054
01:38:16,640 --> 01:38:20,730
I feel as though I have known that
gentleman since a long time ago.

1055
01:38:21,850 --> 01:38:22,940
Lupin...

1056
01:38:22,940 --> 01:38:25,150
I'm sure...
I'm sure we'll meet again.

1057
01:38:30,320 --> 01:38:32,570
She was a nice girl, wasn't she?

1058
01:38:34,830 --> 01:38:37,660
You could stay behind, you know.

1059
01:38:40,920 --> 01:38:42,500
Oh? Fujicakes!

1060
01:38:42,500 --> 01:38:45,040
Lupin, take a look at what I scored!

1061
01:38:45,420 --> 01:38:47,960
Hey! Those are the master printing
plates for the counterfeit bills!

1062
01:38:47,960 --> 01:38:50,300
Wow! Wow! I'd love to be your friend!

1063
01:38:50,300 --> 01:38:51,050
So long!

1064
01:38:51,050 --> 01:38:52,220
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa...

1065
01:38:52,220 --> 01:38:55,470
H-H-H-H-Hey! Hold on a second there!

1066
01:38:58,270 --> 01:39:00,730
Aw, crap, here comes Pops again.

1067
01:39:01,100 --> 01:39:03,690
Lupin, you won't get away this time!

1068
01:39:23,010 --> 01:39:29,760
<i>Fin</i>

